- Accenture plc is an Irish-American professional services company based in Dublin, specializing in information technology services and consulting. A Fortune Global 500 company, it reported revenues of $61.6 billion in 2022.
It helps the world's leading businesses, governments and other organizations build their digital core, optimize their operations, accelerate revenue growth and enhance citizen services

Accenture was established in the year 1989 and was initially known as Andersen Consulting. Accenture changed its name in 2001 after breaking ties with its parent company Arthur Andersen.

- We believe that transparency builds trust
- 47% of the total workforce -> women
- 97% renewable electricity in our locations
• Our total carbon emissions decreased by 68% from our baseline
• 99% of our e-waste relating to computers and workstations was reused or recycled
• 98% of our people completed Ethics & Compliance training
• 1.6M+ people worldwide equipped with the skills to make substantive improvements to their lives
- Accenture revenue for the twelve months ending May 31, 2023 was $63.550B, a 6.65% increase year-over-year
- more than 200 countries, 120+ cities
- 738K employees all over the world
- goal is to achieve net zero emmisions by the year 2025
- Accenture has been on Ethisphere's world's most ethical companies list since 2008.
